NOTE: 

    If you plan on replacing OpenSSL with LibreSSL, then it is at your 
    own risk. I have only tested it on a core CRUX system without any
    of opt or contrib ports installed.

    Download all the source files needed. So libressl, wget, exim, 
    openssh, curl and bindutils. Edit the Pkgfile for wget and add 
    --with-libressl. Do not remove the line --with-ssl=openssl.

    Edit /var/lib/pkg/prt-get.aliases and add the line: 
    libressl: openssl

    Edit /etc/pkgadd.conf and add the line:
    UPGRADE   ^var/lib/pkg/prt-get.aliases$ NO

    Remove openssl port.

    Install libressl port.

    Rebuild wget, exim, openssh, bindutils and curl.

